cross(Vec2, Vec2) - Static method in class camzup.core.Vec2
Returns the z component of the cross product between two vectors.
cross(Vec3, Vec3, Vec3) - Static method in class camzup.core.Vec3
The cross product returns a vector perpendicular to both a and b, and therefore normal to the plane on which a and b rest.

a x b := ( ay bz - az by , az bx - ax bz , ax by - ay bx )

The cross product is anti-commutative, meaning a x b = - ( b x a ) .

inverse(Quaternion, Quaternion) - Static method in class camzup.core.Quaternion
Finds the inverse, or reciprocal, of a quaternion, which is the conjugate divided by the magnitude squared.

a-1 := a* / |a|2

If a quaternion is of unit length, its inverse is equal to its conjugate.

Returns the identity if the quaternion cannot be inverted.

invSqrtUnchecked(float) - Static method in class camzup.core.Utils
An inverse square root implementation for single precision real numbers based on the 'evil bit hack' from Quake III, as described by Chris Lomont in "Fast Inverse Square Root." For accuracy, the result is refined three times with the Newton-Raphson method.

Useful when normalizing vectors or quaternions.

perpendicularCCW(Vec2, Vec2) - Static method in class camzup.core.Vec2
Finds the perpendicular of a vector in the counter-clockwise direction, such that perp ( right ) = forward,
perp ( 1.0, 0.0 ) = ( 0.0, 1.0 ) perp ( forward ) = left,
perp ( 0.0, 1.0 ) = ( -1.0, 0.0 ) perp ( left ) = back,
perp ( -1.0, 0.0 ) = ( 0.0, -1.0 ) perp ( back ) = right,
perp ( 0.0, -1.0 ) = ( 1.0, 0.0 ) In terms of the components, perp ( x, y ) = ( -y, x ) .
perpendicularCW(Vec2, Vec2) - Static method in class camzup.core.Vec2
Finds the perpendicular of a vector in the clockwise direction, such that perp ( right ) = back,
perp( 1.0, 0.0 ) = ( 0.0, -1.0 ) perp ( back ) = left,
perp( 0.0, -1.0 ) = ( -1.0, 0.0 ) perp ( left ) = forward,
perp( -1.0, 0.0 ) = ( 0.0, 1.0 ) perp ( forward ) = right,
perp( 0.0, 1.0 ) = ( 1.0, 0.0 ) In terms of the components, perp ( x, y ) = ( y, -x ) .

sharedCoord(Edge2, Edge2) - Static method in class camzup.core.Edge2
Tests to see if two edges share a vertex coordinate: Returns -1 when a's origin is b's destination. Returns -2 when a's destination is b's destination Returns 1 when a's destination is b's origin. Returns 2 when a's origin is b's origin. Returns 0 when none of the above conditions are met. Assuming a mesh is properly wound, a value of 1 implies that two edges belong to the same face; of 2, different neighboring faces.
sharedCoord(Edge3, Edge3) - Static method in class camzup.core.Edge3
Tests to see if two edges share a vertex coordinate: Returns -1 when a's origin is b's destination. Returns -2 when a's destination is b's destination Returns 1 when a's destination is b's origin. Returns 2 when a's origin is b's origin. Returns 0 when none of the above conditions are met. If the left and right comparisand are the same, returns 2.
